    "noInvoices": "No invoices available.",
    "cancellationConfirmed": "Cancellation confirmed",
    "termsText": "FRI2PLAN - Terms of Use\n\nLast updated: April 2026\n\n1. ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS\nBy using FRI2PLAN, you agree to these terms. If you do not accept these terms, please do not use the application.\n\n2. SERVICE DESCRIPTION\nFRI2PLAN is a family organiser application for managing shared calendars, tasks with rewards, meals, budget, shopping lists, messaging and notes between family members.\n\n3. USER ACCOUNT\nYou are responsible for the confidentiality of your credentials. You must be at least 13 years old to use this service. You agree to provide accurate information and maintain the security of your password.\n\n4. PREMIUM SUBSCRIPTION\nPremium subscription is available at CHF 4.99/month or CHF 39.99/year. A free 14-day trial is offered. Subscription renews automatically unless cancelled from the application settings.\n\n5. PERSONAL DATA\nYour data is processed in accordance with our privacy policy, GDPR and Swiss DPA. We never sell your data to third parties.\n\n6. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY\nAll application content (texts, images, logos, code) is the property of FRI2PLAN. Any reproduction is prohibited without written authorisation.\n\n7. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\nThe application is provided \"as is\". FRI2PLAN cannot be held liable for data loss or service interruptions. Our liability is limited to amounts paid in the last 12 months.\n\n8. CHANGES TO TERMS\nWe reserve the right to modify these terms. Users will be notified by email or in-app notification.\n\n9. APPLICABLE LAW\nThese terms are governed by Swiss law. Any dispute falls under the jurisdiction of Swiss courts.\n\nContact: support@fri2plan.ch",
    "privacyText": "FRI2PLAN - Privacy Policy\n\nLast updated: April 2026\n\n1. DATA CONTROLLER\nFRI2PLAN, Switzerland. Contact: support@fri2plan.ch\n\n2. DATA COLLECTED\n- Account information: name, email, profile photo\n- Usage data: events, tasks, meals, messages, budget, notes\n- Technical data: device, app version, IP address\n\n3. PURPOSES OF PROCESSING\n- Providing and improving the FRI2PLAN service\n- Sending notifications and summary emails (if enabled)\n- Secure billing (via Stripe)\n- Detection of fraudulent activity\n\n4. LEGAL BASIS\nContract performance (Terms of Use) and legitimate interest for service improvement. Explicit consent for marketing communications.\n\n5. RETENTION\nYour data is retained for the duration of your account. Upon deletion, data is permanently erased within 30 days.\n\n6. DATA SHARING\nYour data is not sold. It may be shared with:\n- Stripe (secure payments)\n- Resend (email delivery)\n- WonderPush (push notifications)\n\n7. YOUR RIGHTS (GDPR / DPA)\nRight of access, rectification, erasure, portability, objection.\nExercise your rights at: support@fri2plan.ch\n\n8. SECURITY\nYour data is encrypted in transit (HTTPS/TLS) and at rest. Passwords are hashed with bcrypt.\n\n9. COOKIES\nThe mobile application does not use cookies. The web version uses only essential technical cookies.\n\nDPO contact: support@fri2plan.ch",
